title.narrative: PLANNING, MONITORING AND EVALUATION

description.narrative: UNICEF staff and partners have access to guidance, tools and resources to effectively plan, monitor and evaluate country programme outcomes., which contributes to Cross-Sectoral - Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses, Cross-Sectoral - Planning And Programme Reviews, Evaluation, Research. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Data, Research, Evaluation And Knowledge Management, Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Programmes are efficiently designed, coordinated, managed and supported to meet quality programming standards in achieving results for children in development and humanitarian setting.

description.narrative: The;internal programme review at mid-term indicate good progress at output level despite the impact of COVID-19. However, outcome indicators are increasingly off track. Key adjustments to the programme prioritizing the recovery from the pandemic was agreed with counterparts. In terms of data management, UNICEF Philippines effectiveness influenced the design of the Demographic and Health Survey (DHS) to include key Children data gaps. Engagement with the Community-Based Monitoring System (CBMS) will lead to stronger data for children at subnational level in 2022.; | Status:On-track | As-of Date:17/12/2021
